de.oaam.model.oaam.capabilities

Interface TaskOnDeviceCapability

  • All Superinterfaces:
    CapabilityA, org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, ModeDependentElementA, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier, OaamBaseElementA, VariantDependentElementA
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    TaskOnDeviceCapabilityImpl

    public interface TaskOnDeviceCapability
extends CapabilityA, OaamBaseElementA, VariantDependentElementA, ModeDependentElementA
    A representation of the model object 'Task On Device Capability'. A possible allocations of a task to a device.

    The following features are supported:

    • Task Type
    • Device Type
    • Worst Case Execution Time
    • Failure Probability
    See Also:
    CapabilitiesPackage.getTaskOnDeviceCapability()

      • getWorstCaseExecutionTime

        float getWorstCaseExecutionTime()
        Returns the value of the 'Worst Case Execution Time' attribute. The default value is "0.0". The worst case execution time of the tasks in s. This time must be independent from the inputs and makes only sense, if the task behaves deterministic.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Worst Case Execution Time' attribute.
        See Also:
        setWorstCaseExecutionTime(float), CapabilitiesPackage.getTaskOnDeviceCapability_WorstCaseExecutionTime()
